INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (375801, 'It’s like my whole life my left ring finger has been lacking something, and finally it feels complete.', 25959, 0), (375802, 'She begins, “What is the question we spend our entire lives asking?” and answers, “Our question is this: Are we loved? I don’t mean by one another.” She closes her sermon to the snakes with these words: “I am like you, curious and small. Like you, I pause alertly and open my senses to try to read the air, the clouds, the sun’s slant, the little movements of the animals, all in the hope I will learn the secret of whether I am loved.', 24743, 0), (375803, 'Every woman should feel like a princess on her wedding day', 59871, 0), (375804, '... it is easier to tell someone closer to you before you tell your partner.', 25959, 0), (375805, 'The fact that I am marrying the man of my dreams is all that matters.', 25959, 0), (375806, 'Instead I’ve built a house made of lies that have come crashing down around me.', 25959, 0), (375807, 'The secret is to keep yourself interesting.', 17002, 0), (375808, 'But there was something in his eyes at times that I would almost swear said something more. Some deeper sort of regard.', 15629, 0), (375809, 'Are you afraid in there?" she said softly, as the men called out for them."No," he said. "I''m not afraid. You lock me in. They won''t get me."She closed the door on the little white face, turned the key in the lock. Then she slipped the key into her pocket. The lock was hidden by a pivoting device shaped like a light switch. It was impossible to see the outline of the cupboard in the paneling of the wall. Yes, he''d be safe there. She was sure of it.The girl murmured his name and laid her palm flat on the wooden panel."I''ll come back for you later. I promise.', 38243, 0), (375810, 'The truth is, far too many people in our culture do not know what love is. And this not knowing feels like a terrible secret, a lack that we have to cover up.', 218, 0), (375811, 'Sign this... and I''ll show you', 40824, 0), (375812, 'I flow like a butter in the nailed pan I stole. I also kept the nail, to polish and use as a means of teleportation.', 3544, 0), (375813, 'Once you open up a secret, it starts leaking out all over.', 7775, 0), (375814, 'The deeply secretive cannot grasp that protecting your secret too fiercely exposes it.', 18806, 0), (375815, 'The secret to happiness is to never make it dependent on that which can be taken away', 10137, 0), (375816, 'There are other ways than conventional doors to get around my house, Ms Rainn.', 22200, 0), (375817, 'What is the use of the colon? What is a colon? Generally it opens onto an explanation, but it is always done with the help of an interruption. It can be said that the colon is not the period, it is the period of the period, the canceling of the period. It is a moment mute and marked; it is the most delicate tattoo of the text. It is also in place of, instead of, everything that would be causal. For example, when we read: "It''s simply that: secret." "Secret," is a sentence, it is the shortest sentence perhaps. But it is a sentence in one word. It is a sentence that is secret and that at the same time says its name. One could invert and say: "Secret: it is simply that." This is secret, the secret is the secret of this, it is a word which makes infinite sense all by itself, it is a sentence which performs the secret itself [Clarice Lispector, The Stream of Life, trans Elizabeth Lowe & Earl Fitz, Foreword by Hélène Cixous trans Verena Conley, Minneapolis: University of Minnesota Press, 1989]', 3219, 0), (375818, 'Dear Anonymous, I''ve got a secret I know you can keep it because you don''t really exist....This is what shapes you, this is what makes you as authentic as you are fake.', 11690, 0), (375819, 'It was the only lie she ever told. She did not do it to protect Francisco; she did it because she felt, for some reason which she could not define, that the incident was a secret too precious to share.', 631, 0), (375820, 'I''d never forget how it felt to say those words. To be in our place. In love with you, in love with us, in love with our secret, with the island we were building, keeping out the whole wide world.', 23416, 0), (375821, 'Pip wondered what the secret was of being different in a way that attracted people, as opposed to her own way.', 5212, 0), (375822, 'Invoking the moral high ground somehow makes you lose it. Using a secret as a weapon makes you almost as bad as the transgressor.', 251, 0), (375823, 'Most of my life has been spent keeping information close, turning it over and over in my mind. The impulse to share anything is a new one, the impulse to hide as natural as breathing.', 73, 0), (375824, 'The secret to happiness is a good sense of humor with adult content.', 59872, 0), (375825, 'We''ve talked, and alot has been said ,but no words were uttered at all', 6900, 0), (375826, 'Secret of success is something that will outlast in the life of human being.', 23468, 0), (375827, 'That is her secret. A poor and precious secret that not even the executioners, the decrees, the occupying authorities, the Depot, the barracks, the camps, History, time-everything that defiles and destroys you-have been able to take away from her.', 33077, 0), (375828, 'Everyone who keeps a secret, itches to tell it.', 236, 0), (375829, 'The secret of a successful life isn''t the success but happiness.', 2586, 0), (375830, 'Secretly we fear ourselves, not the fear itself.', 2586, 0), (375831, 'The secret of life is love, but the purpose of life is happiness.', 2586, 0), (375832, 'Life was beautiful, but it was also painful. People fail, a few get up, but there’s never a guarantee that their second attempt will work out.', 6600, 0), (375833, 'Every human is born of collusion. We come into this world the result of a covenant. Sometimes made of love. Sometimes of circumstance. But almost always made in secret.', 15996, 0), (375834, 'Nearly everyone has had a box of secret pain, shared with no one.', 1070, 0), (375835, 'The Secret of Happiness is to admire without desiring. And that is not happiness.', 10650, 0), (375836, 'Never share you secret with a married person for the partner will get to hear of it.', 25197, 0), (375837, 'His worried face falls away and is replaced with what can only be described as a glow--like someone who has a terrific secret and they''re about to let you in on it.', 59873, 0), (375838, 'even though I think that Mia and I have enough secrets between the two of us at this point', 150, 0), (375839, 'Music is heard in the background. As the movemnt becomes sharper; the many dancers acting but as one. She is one with her secret. As the time draws near, the woman''s body begins to push. With the rhythm of the music and the beat of the dancer''s feet; her secret almost revealed.', 31757, 0), (375840, 'It was as though he had secrets, and he wanted you to know he would keep them for the pleasure of depriving you of their taste.', 6722, 0), (375841, 'There is a secret about human love that is commonly overlooked: Receiving it is much more scary and threatening than giving it.', 39566, 0), (375842, 'Of this poetryI’m left with the emptinessof an endless secret', 59874, 0), (375843, 'Because after a time having a secret and nobody knowing you have a secret is no fun. And although you don''t want others to know what the secret is, you want them to at least know you have one.', 1541, 0), (375844, 'If your inner silence begins to wear a silk fruit; only then, the day will reveal to you its hidden secret.', 23464, 0), (375845, 'Let me tell you a secret, a tremendous and wonderful secret. Let me share with you something so valuable that any schoolboy would gladly trade his most treasured procession to find out what I shall tell you.', 27609, 0), (375846, 'She wasn''t my kind of woman and that''s why, that night she was. This wine is the Blood of Christ. Brings the truth out of a woman sooner than any confession box does. Makes you trust a stranger with your life, your car keys, your best-guarded secret.', 34073, 0), (375847, 'Do you want to hear it or not? You have to keep it a secret.“ I would pluck out my own eyes with a fork before I would give away your secrets, “ Simon said, then looked anxious. “ Wait a second. Do you think that„s likely to be required?', 39, 0), (375848, 'When the dog bites, when the bee stings... I simply remember I have a boyfriend and suddenly things don''t seem quite so completely shit.', 173, 0), (375849, 'He is stronger than anyone I know, & warmer than anyone else realizes; he is a secret that I have kept, & will keep, for the rest of my life.', 73, 0), (375850, 'It was gentler here, softer, its seethe the quietest of whispers, as if, in deference to a drawing room, it had quite deliberately put on its ''manners''; it kept itself out of sight, obliterated itself, but distinctly with an air of saying, ''Ah, but just wait! Wait till we are alone together! Then I will begin to tell you something new! Something white! something cold! something sleepy! something of cease, and peace, and the long bright curve of space! Tell them to go away. Banish them. Refuse to speak. Leave them, go upstairs to your room, turn out the light and get into bed - I will go with you, I will be waiting for you, I will tell you a better story than Little Kay of the Skates, or The Snow Ghost - I will surround your bed, I will close the windows, pile a deep drift against the door, so that none will ever again be able to enter. Speak to them!...'' It seemed as if the little hissing voice came from a slow white spiral of falling flakes in the corner by the front window - but he could not be sure.("Silent Snow, Secret Snow")', 26665, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (375851, 'Come with me to howling tree?""What?""Howling tree. It''s a place a found. Come on', 53134, 0), (375852, 'A fellowship of secret scholars spent five hundred years on this task. Now we''re penciling it in for a Friday morning.', 3372, 0), (375853, 'Just why it should have happened, or why it should have happened just when it did, he could not, of course, possibly have said; nor perhaps could it even have occurred to him to ask. The thing was above all a secret, something to be preciously concealed from Mother and Father; and to that very fact it owed an enormous part of its deliciousness. It was like a peculiarly beautiful trinket to be carried unmentioned in one''s trouser-pocket - a rare stamp, an old coin, a few tiny gold links found trodden out of shape on the path in the park, a pebble of carnelian, a sea shell distinguishable from all others by an unusual spot or stripe-and, as if it were anyone of these, he carried around with him everywhere a warm and persistent and increasingly beautiful sense of possession. Nor was it only a sense of possession - it was also a sense of protection. It was as if, in some delightful way, his secret gave him a fortress, a wall behind which he could retreat into heavenly seclusion.("Silent Snow, Secret Snow")', 26665, 0), (375854, 'Miles smiled. "Can you keep a secret?"Bea snorted. "Did I tell you what you were in for if you married my daughter?""No," Miles conceded."Well, then," she said, as if that settled the matter.', 8957, 0), (375855, 'Her aunt Sol had once told Shai to smile at the worst insults and snap at the minor ones. That way, no man would know your heart.', 508, 0), (375856, 'I also like ladies. And not as in shopping buddies, but in the carnal sense.', 1524, 0), (375857, 'Love should never be a secret and it should never, ever be forgotten.', 3818, 0), (375858, 'Everyone’s got secrets, Jem. It’s what makes people interesting.', 7968, 0), (375859, 'Only bad books have good endings.if a book is any good, its ending is always bad_because byou don''t want the book to end.', 2198, 0), (375860, 'Nonsense. Everyone knows Canadians are a peaceful people.” He was laughing now.“Tell that to the White House circa 1812,” I told him.“Oh? Why?”“Because that’s the year the peace-loving Canadians burned it to the ground.”Dominick grabbed an empty bottle and jumped onto his chair. The room got silent in an instant as everyone paused to look at him. “Cheers to 1812.” He lifted his empty bottle.The whole room whooped and raised their full glasses, howling in unison.I could barely hear over the sound of my own laughter.', 43996, 0), (375861, 'Every personal existence was upheld by a secret.', 1390, 0), (375862, 'May knowledge come to us! What is this secret our heart has understood and yet will not reveal to us, although it seems to beat as if it were endeavoring to tell it?', 631, 0), (375863, 'There is no secret formula--only a life committed to a close walk with God.', 16666, 0), (375864, 'Freemasonry is relevant as much as the actions of Freemasons are meaningful.', 26550, 0), (375865, 'We''re nobody''s dirty little secret.', 38648, 0), (375866, 'For so long, it was just my secret. It burned inside me, and I felt like I was carrying something important, something that made me who I was and made me different from everybody else. I took it with me everywhere, and there was never a moment when I wasn''t aware of it. It was like I was totally awake, like I could feel every nerve ending in my body. Sometimes my skin would almost hurt from the force of it, that''s how strong it was. Like my whole body was buzzing or something. I felt almost, I don''t know, noble, like a medieval knight or something, carrying this secret love around with me.', 9830, 0), (375867, '...and here''s a secret for you - everything beautiful is sad...gilded with impermanence...', 4795, 0), (375868, 'Would you please do me the honor of telling me WHAT THE BLAZES IS GOING ON?', 371, 0), (375869, 'The secret is writing down one simple line after another.', 78, 0), (375870, 'The secret island had looked mysterious enough on the night they had seen it before - but now, swimming in the hot June haze, it seemed more enchanting than ever. As they drew near to it, and saw the willow trees that bent over the water-edge and heard the sharp call of moorhens that scuttled off, the children gazed in delight. Nothing but trees and birds and little wild animals. Oh, what a secret island, all for their very own, to live on and play on.', 15790, 0), (375871, 'I’m bored to death. Perhaps I should pillage one of my neighbors for my own amusement. It seems to work for Drowden.', 371, 0), (375872, 'King Drowden has given his men instructions to infiltrate the town, bribe townspeople for the secrets of their neighbors, steal the neighbors’ hidden treasures. Much more subtle than Drowden’s usual smash and burn technique. We do hope Drowden isn’t growing a brain.', 371, 0), (375873, 'There are skeletons in everyone''s closet, things no one ever wants the world to discover.', 21, 0), (375874, 'It is better to have ten skeletons in your closet, than walk with no bones.', 3341, 0), (375875, 'Weird, even for one of us. Or maybe she''s worse.""Worse how?""Normal.', 180, 0), (375876, 'Tell me, how do get away from your own self?” she questioned. I knew what she meant with a sickening realization. They knew what I was. Somehow, they had found out my only secret.', 6463, 0), (375877, '[on why he considers Marlon Brando and Jean-Louis Trintignant to be his favorite actors] They don''t externalize or project everything. They keep a mystery within themselves, and that I think is the sign of a truly great actor, to be able to maintain that.', 35830, 0), (375878, 'Lest others should attempt the ascent of this terrible climb and perish, they swore themselves to secrecy (telling only enough people to ensure the perpetuation of their epic) and went off to try Everest instead.', 34699, 0), (375879, 'The great secret in salam is it brings love, tranquility and peace to the person receiving the greeting.', 29626, 0), (375880, 'If someone offered the chance to be happy for the rest of your life, everyone in the room will bid, but what they don''t know that the secret is nothing, they all have the power already with them.One of the most bizarre quirks of human beings is that they have always craved for happiness and yet have always found it difficult to find the things that would really make them happy. The everlasting happiness cannot be achieved through other people or the materialistic things.', 59875, 0), (375881, 'Sometimes, the wicked will tell us things just to confuse us–to haunt our thoughts long after we''ve faced them.', 343, 0), (375882, 'I hope that real love and truth are stronger in the end than any evil or misfortune in the world.', 96, 0), (375883, 'People couldn''t become truly holy, he said, unless they also had the opportunity to be definitively wicked.', 195, 0), (375884, 'Goodness is something chosen. When a man cannot choose he ceases to be a man.', 1132, 0), (375885, 'The best men are not consistent in good—why should the worst men be consistent in evil?', 3317, 0), (375886, 'You—you were like me. You were a child. A normal child. And that was taken from you.”“Does that bother you?”“Well, it certainly makes you harder to hate.', 1726, 0), (375887, 'You are good when you walk to your goal firmly and with bold steps.Yet you are not evil when you go thither limping.For those who limp go not backwards.But you who are strong and swift, see that you do not limp before the lame, deeming it kindness.', 81, 0), (375888, 'Being against evil doesn''t make you good. Tonight I was against it and then I was evil myself. I could feel it coming just like a tide... I just want to destroy them. But when you start taking pleasure in it you are awfully close to the thing you''re fighting.', 110, 0), (375889, 'Maybe it’s not as clear-cut as that. Maybe it’s the very presence of one thing – light or darkness – that necessitates the existence of the other.Think about it, people couldn’t become legendary heroes if they hadn’t first done something to combat darkness. Doctors could do no good if thereweren’t diseases for them to treat.', 13269, 0), (375890, 'One thing yo learn when you''ve lived as long as I have-people aren''t all good, and people aren''t all bad. We move in and out of darkness and light all of our lives. Right now, I''m pleased to be in the light.', 2433, 0), (375891, 'And one of the elders of the city , said , speak to us of good and evil.And he answered :You are good in countless ways , and you are not evil when you are not good .', 81, 0), (375892, 'It''s going to be like an...aura, I guess."He looked down at me and raised an eyebrow. "Explain?""Like even though there are outside forces pushing through the walls, in here it''s like a bubble of goodness. Like coming home."I could feel him smiling and it encouraged me to elaborate. "When I think of how others would see it, I imagine them seeing a force of goodness overshadowing a force of evil, protecting it.', 13269, 0), (375893, 'Perhaps man was neither good nor bad, was only a machine in an insensate universe--his courage no more than a reflex to danger, like the automatic jump at the pin-prick. Perhaps there were no virtues, unless jumping at pin-pricks was a virtue, and humanity only a mechanical donkey led on by the iron carrot of love, through the pointless treadmill of reproduction.', 407, 0), (375894, 'Within the infant rind of this small flowerPoison hath residence and medicine power.For this, being smelt, with that part cheers each part;Being tasted, stays all senses with the heart.Two such opposèd kings encamp them still,In man as well as herbs—grace and rude will. And where the worser is predominant,Full soon the canker death eats up that plant.(Inside the little rind of this weak flower, there is both poison and powerful medicine. If you smell it, you feel good all over your body. But if you taste it, you die. There are two opposite elements in everything, in men as well as in herbs—good and evil. When evil is dominant, death soon kills the body like cancer.) ', 13, 0), (375895, 'Good and Evil are opposite points on a circle, Dr. Chiver. Greater good is just halfway back to Bad.', 38636, 0), (375896, 'And I reckon them that are good must suffer for it the same as them that are bad.', 344, 0), (375897, 'Men who believe in good and evil, and who believe that good should win, should watch for those moments when it is possible to play God', 850, 0), (375898, 'Deep inside, the majority of people had the sneaking suspicion that evil was more powerful than good and could be counteracted only by more evil.', 36327, 0), (375899, 'There are two godheads: the world and my independent I. I am either happy or unhappy, that is all. It can be said: good or evil do not exist. A man who is happy must have no fear. Not even in the face of death. Only a man who lives not in time but in the present is happy.', 1163, 0), (375900, 'Don''t make another''s pain the source of your own happiness.', 13072, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (375901, 'Simply put...there is a vast ocean of shit that you people don''t know shit ab', 59876, 0), (375902, 'It is well, I think, for us to learn to tell evil from good; but it has its price, as everything does. We leave our evil friend behind.', 3759, 0), (375903, 'Sully disapproved of destruction for destruction''s sake, which seemed ever more popular in the modern world, but he always took delight in burning out or otherwise eliminating Evil when Evil just couldn''t keep its ugly head down and stay in the shadows, when it came right at you with all teeth bared. The world needed a little Evil, so Good had something to compare itself to, but you couldn''t let it think it had the right-of-way on the road and an invitation to dinner.', 591, 0), (375904, 'There is no one who is completely evil as to lack some goodness in him.', 3682, 0), (375905, 'Before eating from the tree of knowledge, Adam and Eve had no notion of Good and evil.They were kicked out of paradise, because the supposed Creator was unable to reason that giving someone free will to choose between two things while having no notion of either, would be the Himalaya of nonsense.', 11631, 0), (375906, 'Most modern reproducers of life, even including the camera, really repudiate it. We gulp down evil, choke at good.', 2547, 0), (375907, 'There isn''t any good or bad, everything is either a product of pure awareness or sheer ignorance!', 12721, 0), (375908, 'But while I have never considered myself a very good person, neither can I bring myself to believe that I am spectacularly bad one. Perhaps it''s simply impossible to think of oneself in such a way.', 1269, 0), (375909, '[But] I fear that in the individual lives of all but a few, the balance is in debit - we do so little that is positive good, even if we negatively avoid what is actively evil.', 65, 0), (375910, 'There is more evil than good when we preach the miracle centered gospel instead if the kingdom gospel.', 3800, 0), (375911, 'I have to tell you the truth. But you are too ugly for it.', 4618, 0), (375912, 'Right and wrong stood for him as immutable as the two poles. He had never wandered in that twilight country where the nuances of evil and good cast their perplexing shadows.', 5869, 0), (375913, 'Although Quirrell couldn’t fend off the dark allure of power, he did provide Harry with a lesson that guided him through the rest of his school career: there is no such thing as good and evil. We become the choices that we make.', 59877, 0), (375914, 'One man''s god is another man''s devil.', 40101, 0), (375915, 'The little mutton-chopped man interrupted them to point out that in his opinion good was not the avoidance of evil, but something more positive than that: it was making the world a better place.', 14, 0), (375916, 'We''re the gray area, angel. We''re the pieces of the puzzle they don''t know what to do with, the pieces that don''t quite fit into their perfect little picture, so they choose to discard us, to keep their image untainted, but we can only be ignored for so long. Because eventually, whether they want to admit it or not, all of their black and white will bleed together anyway.', 364, 0), (375917, 'Well, let folly be our cloak, a veil before the eyes of the Enemy! For he is very wise, and weighs all things to a nicety in the scales of his malice. But the only measure that he knows is desire, desire for power; and so he judges all hearts. Into his heart the thought will not enter that any will refuse it, that having the Ring we may seek to destroy it. If we seek this, we shall put him out of reckoning.', 65, 0), (375918, 'You know,” Naomi said, “if you’re looking at hundreds of people burning to death as a problem solving itself, that may be more evidence that you’re on wrong side.', 13363, 0), (375919, 'I love you all - if you are not people!', 4618, 0), (375920, 'Unto the pure ‪#‎ALL‬ things are pure: but unto them that are defiled and unbelieving is nothing pure; but even their mind and conscience is defiled.Titus 1:15.Dinesh Samuel Thank you.THEY SEE EVIL IN YOU BECUASE THEY ARE FULL OF IT.some so called Believers think am against the message. some so called Unbelievers think am going crazy and defends the message. They are all right, because I BELONG TO JESUS ALONE. In Christ Alone.1 Corinthians 13:7 kjv6 Rejoiceth not in iniquity, but rejoiceth in the truth; 7Beareth all things, believeth all things, hopeth all things, endureth all things. 8Charity never faileth: but whether there be prophecies, they shall fail; whether there be tongues, they shall cease; whether there be knowledge, it shall vanish away. 9For we know in part, and we prophesy in part. 10But when that which is perfect is come, then that which is in part shall be done away.', 18372, 0), (375921, 'That''s who I am, a man who has been both good and evil throughout his life. pg 14', 34, 0), (375922, 'I lost the most precious thing a man can have: my faith in my fellow man. I laughed and I wept at God''s irony, at the absurd way he had chosen to demonstrate to me that I was an instrument of Good and Evil.', 34, 0), (375923, 'You''re not trying to find the answer to a question, you''re simply trying to confirm something you desperately want to believe: that everyone is evil.', 34, 0), (375924, '...she was betting on the fact that people were basically good, despite all the Evil in the world.', 34, 0), (375925, 'I love you as I do all - not at all.', 4618, 0), (375926, 'The thing is, you can''t ever really know how rotten someone will turn out to be.', 3253, 0), (375927, 'Good and bad are not opposites, they are both just different forms of intensity.', 539, 0), (375928, 'May you fear no evil. ...And may evil fear you.', 4104, 0), (375929, 'There was something strange in my sensations, indescribably new and incredibly sweet. I knew myself, at the first breath of this new life, to be tenfold more wicked and the thought delighted me like wine.', 449, 0), (375930, 'I used to think this was all about good and evil,” said Rickett, “but it’s not.”“No?”“There’s a kind of evil that isn’t even in opposition to good, because good is an irrelevance to it. It’s a foulness that’s right at the heart of existence, born with the stuff of the universe. It’s in the decay to which all things tend. It is, and it always will be, but in dying we leave it behind.”“And while we’re alive?”“We set our souls against it, and our saints and angels, too.” He patted Parker on the shoulder. “Especially the destroying ones.', 1786, 0), (375931, 'Nothing in the Grimmerie on how to depose a tyrant - nothing useful... Nothing there that described why men and women could turn out so horrible. Or so wonderful - if that ever happens anymore.', 1632, 0), (375932, 'So, your god is the only god? Okay, but then, so is my dog.', 4618, 0), (375933, 'The sooner the jihadis go up to their imagined #heaven, the sooner our earth would be a heaven.', 4618, 0), (375934, 'Never think taking a life is easy. Do that and in a way they win.', 1190, 0), (375935, 'Having ''holy'' thoughts, and doing bad deeds, such a lot are assholes indeed.', 4618, 0), (375936, 'I love all life as my own. Therefore, I say, you''re my very own. But am I, an infidel who does not believe in your ism, also your own?', 4618, 0), (375937, 'The line dividing good and evil cuts through the heart of every human being.', 2564, 0), (375938, 'Right or wrong is nonexistent in the eye of the universe. It doesn''t matter who is right or who is wrong because the universe never cares for both. The universe lets both happen and the universe lets both end. A natural disaster claims all lives. Life and resources is the one that matters. No matter who you are or what you are, you must never harm life and you must never spend resources. These are what matters. I don''t know about the afterlife. I don''t know whether the afterlife exists, but in this existence, these are what matters.', 21770, 0), (375939, 'You''ve sinned, I suppose, but your punishment has been out of all proportion. They have turned you into something other than a human being. You have no power of choice any longer. You are committed to socially acceptable acts, a little machine capable only of good.', 1132, 0), (375940, 'The heresy of an age of reason. I see what is right and approve, but I do what is wrong.', 1132, 0), (375941, 'Babies aren''t born cruel or filled with sick desire. Evil is not intrinsic. It''s fashioned.', 431, 0), (375942, 'I, on the other hand, am very concerned about how word choice will affect my readers. For instance, in the description of Genesis, I chose the term ''good and evil'' instead of ''right and wrong'', which are basically two same terms. I wanted to use ''right and wrong'' because it definitely will ignite more controversies than ''good and evil'', but I chose to use the latter because I was afraid of the social influence that can come from reading my book, and although there is no adult material at all in the book, I could risk getting my book banned.', 21770, 0), (375943, 'There are no heroes and there are no villains. There are just opposing points of view. That''s all history is...the viciously long battle between world views.', 13219, 0), (375944, 'Some people would say- you''re only a drop, your word-breaking is only a drop, it wouldn''t matter. But all the evil in the world''s made up of little drops. It''s silly talking about the unimportance of the little drops. The little drops and the ocean are the same thing.', 1452, 0), (375945, 'I had no idea you were capable of such a diabolical plan, Human, my friend, just human, the devil doesn’t make plans, anyway, if men were good, he wouldn’t even exist.', 1357, 0), (375946, 'Well some are born to be hanged, and some are not; and many of those who are not hanged are much worse than those who are.', 59878, 0), (375947, 'Evil people relate more to the black pole. It''s - this is not exact, of course, as the science of magic is as complex as the magic of electronics - it''s like traveling past a mountain. The white pole is at the apex, and it is an exhilarating height, but it takes a lot of work and few missteps to ascend it. The black pole is at the nadir, and it is easy to walk downhill; sometimes you can just sit down and slide or roll and, if you fall, you can get there very fast indeed. If you don''t pay attention to where you''re going, you''ll tend to go down, because it is the course of least resistance. Since the average person has only the vaguest notion where he is going and tends to shut out awareness of the consequence of evil, he inevitably drifts downward. There is much more space at the base of the mountain than at the peak!', 9950, 0), (375948, 'Well -- think about this. What if all your actions and choices, good or bad, make no difference to God? What if the pattern is pre-set? No no -- hang on -- this is a question worth struggling with. What if our badness and mistakes are the very thing that set our fate and bring us round to good? What if, for some of us, we can''t get there any other way?', 1269, 0), (375949, 'Not only does evil depend upon good, but in this case, darkness depends upon light.', 59879, 0), (375950, '...in the Twilight Princess worldview, darkness is not necessarily correlated with evil, just as light is not necessarily correlated with good.', 59879, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (375951, 'I believe that there is good in everyone, even an evil pirate such as you.', 20273, 0), (375952, 'Good necessitates evil and the two sides of that disk are not always clearly marked.', 28435, 0), (375953, 'Happiness is a fortress.', 26714, 0), (375954, 'If one cannot gain recognition foranything else, he can rest well with the assurance that he is "good," which in most cases equates with "right". Were it not for an evil to rail against he might just as well never have been born. Yes, evil is the great savior and sustainer of those whocondemn it most.', 3182, 0), (375955, 'I have known many survivors for whom the holocaust is the central them of their lives. They have no other. I have tried to live with tolerance and forgiveness as the theme of my life. God have us the power to be good or evil. This is our choice. Because some pick evil, we must work together to recognize and stop it. But while we survivors may lead the change, we cannot do this alone. It must be the goal of all people. If we will join in this goal, then there is hope for humanity.', 59880, 0), (375956, 'If good men pretend to be villains, how is anybody supposed to know the difference between them?', 2314, 0), (375957, 'Surely God is good to Israel, to those who are pure in heart. But as for me, my feet had almost slipped; I had nearly lost my foothold. For I envied the arrogant when I saw the prosperity of the wicked.', 33, 0), (375958, 'He had memorized the entire Qur''an and lectured on the nature of evil, which, like a shadow, cannot exist independently of the good silhouettes.', 17777, 0), (375959, 'How is it possible that anyone can believe in a kind of God of Evil named Satan or Devil? Surely, evil lies within oneself.', 59881, 0), (375960, 'If one cannot gain recognition for anything else, he can rest well with the assurance that he is "good," which in most cases equates with "right". Were it not for an evil to rail against he might just as well never have been born. Yes, evil is the great savior and sustainer of those who condemn it most.', 3182, 0), (375961, 'Good to evil seems evil a', 567, 0), (375962, 'If the universe is trying to maintain balance, we must aid this by ensuring that Good is not enjoyed excessively. Or else the universe will re-balance itself by creating Evil to counteract Good. That is the purpose of Evil: it balances the Good.', 479, 0), (375963, 'When faced with pain and evil, we have to make a choice.We can choose to be taken by the evil.Or we can try to embrace the good.', 25950, 0), (375964, 'Light and dark ain''t supposed to mix. They''re like broccoli and chocolate - just nasty when you put them together - but that appears to be what''s happening with you', 4894, 0), (375965, 'Whether a character is good or evil depends on your perspective.', 59882, 0), (375966, 'Good does not exist.It is merely an absent of evil.', 59883, 0), (375967, '...or perhaps about acknowledging that life is a delicate balance of great forces, and that good would lose its potency if there was no evil left to fight in the world.', 799, 0), (375968, 'Nature is not kind', 59884, 0), (375969, 'Goodness will always win over evil, no matter how much the evil attempts to break you. More than that, you are never truly in darkness. Sometimes, all you need to do is turn on the light.', 24278, 0), (375970, 'Deep down, she''s a good person, Diana is," Caine said, and sighed. "Deep down, I''m not. But she is.', 817, 0), (375971, 'Those who won''t accept evil never get anything good.', 8978, 0), (375972, 'Beware when wrong-doing is called good and right-doing is called evil.', 4246, 0), (375973, 'A book is a private thing, citizen; it belongs to the one who writes it and to the one who reads it. Like the mind itself, a book is a private space. Within that space, anything is possible. The greatest evil and the greatest good.', 13956, 0), (375974, 'Good and evil has no passport; it speaks in different tongues, wears many skins, and exists everywhere, even in the same person', 59885, 0), (375975, 'Hope starts as a promise made to yourself, the first drop of rain in a parched land, the first step onto dry earth for a shipwreck survivor. It is a listening crowd for a lonely heart.What we hope in must be greater than us; therefore, we will always need something greater than man to believe in. Good and evil may be a necessity to perceive our world, but hope is a prerequisite for life.', 3477, 0), (375976, 'Evil flourishes because the good aren''t good enough," see murmured. "And sometimes the good just have bad days.', 21442, 0), (375977, 'There is more goodness than evil in the world, but you know, you still got to work at it.', 59886, 0), (375978, 'On the one hand, if God is wiser than we His judgement must differ from ours on many things, and not least on good and evil. What seems to us good may therefore not be good in His eyes, and what seems to us evil may not be evil.', 26, 0), (375979, 'You see we do, yet see you but our handsAnd this the bleeding business they have done:Our hearts you see not; they are pitiful', 13, 0), (375980, 'I want to dance always, to be good and not evil, and when it is all over not to have the feeling that I might have done better.', 59887, 0), (375981, 'The greatest power of bureaucracies is to make the smart act stupid and the good to act evil.', 51390, 0), (375982, 'Satan''s survival-of-the-fittest system appears to work- in the short run. But the great controversy is about the long run.', 46733, 0), (375983, 'The disciples of the Baal Shem Tov, the founder of Hasidism, tell of a dream he had. In the dream, the very incarnation of the Evil Impulse appears in the form of a sinister heart. The Baal Shem Tov seizes the heart and pounds it furiously. He would destroy evil and redeem the world. As he pummels it, he hears an infant’s sobbing emitted from the heart. He stops beating it. In the midst of evil is a voice of innocence; there is goodness entangled in evil.', 59888, 0), (375984, 'If 9 out of 10 grandmothers selected from 10 respective cultures can agree it is evil, then it''s evil. Cut it out.', 6029, 0), (375985, 'Whoever hurt you had a choice to hurt you or love you. It was his choice whoever he is, not yours. It is the same as how Hank made the choice to beat on me and Mom instead of loving us the way he should have. As you told me, that was not my fault either. I believe it is the option of choice that makes evil possible. When he made his choice, you really had no choice.” [said Craig]', 32935, 0), (375986, 'Good to evil seems evil', 567, 0), (375987, 'People always equate beauty with good, but it just ain''t so.', 896, 0), (375988, 'And those characters [in a fairy tale] dwell in a moral world, whose laws are as clear as the law of gravity. That too is a great advantage of the folk tale. It is not a failure of imagination to see the sky blue. It is a failure rather to be weary of its being blue- and not to notice how blue it is. And appreciation of the subtler colors of the sky will come later. In the folk tale, good is good and evil is evil, and the former will triumph and later will fail. This is not the result of the imaginative quest. It is rather its principle and foundation. It is what will enable the child later on to understand Macbeth, or Don Quixote, or David Copperfield.', 11675, 0), (375989, 'Good'' did not triumph. ''Evil'' did not triumph. The two resolved, destroyed each other and created new ''evils'', new ''goods'' which slew each other in their turn.', 29111, 0), (375990, 'That''s the world out there, little green apples and infectious disease.', 1582, 0), (375991, 'As for Doing-good...I have tried it fairly, and, strange as it may seem, am satisfied that it does not agree with my constitution.', 1049, 0), (375992, 'Some people misunderstand evil and believe it will relent, and because their misplaced hope inspires dark hearts to dream darker dreams, they are the fathers and mothers of all wars. Evil does not relent; it must be defeated. And even when defeated, uprooted, and purified by fire, evil leaves behind a seed that will one day germinate and, in blooming, again be misunderstood.', 591, 0), (375993, 'I must have flowers, always, and always.', 19729, 0), (375994, 'The violets in the mountains have broken the rocks.', 355, 0), (375995, 'who knows if the moon''sa balloon,coming out of a keen cityin the sky--filled with pretty people?( and if you and I shouldget into it,if theyshould take me and take you into their balloon,why thenwe''d go up higher with all the pretty peoplethan houses and steeples and clouds:go sailingaway and away sailing into a keen city which nobody''s ever visited,wherealways it''s Spring)and everyone''sin love and flowers pick themselves', 37, 0), (375996, 'In joy or sadness flowers are our constant friends.', 2634, 0), (375997, 'Who wants flowers when you''re dead? Nobody.', 268, 0), (375998, 'Butterflies are not insects,'' Captain John Sterling said soberly. ''They are self-propelled flowers.', 17, 0), (375999, 'Raff,'' Katsa said, ''your problem is that your heart''s not in it. We need to find something to strengthen your defensive resolve. What if you pretended he''s trying to smash your favorite medicinal plant?''''The rare blue safflower,'' Bann suggested.''Yes,'' Katsa said gamely, ''pretend he''s after your snaf', 371, 0), (376000, 'The stems stood tall and straight, one series arranged in a single line, the other in a crudely shaped heart, the final one in the shape of the letter U. I love you.', 7800, 0);
